        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1780333684" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17300561472869668514">I don&apos;t remember when I first read this. Probably shortly after Field of Dreams came out. I loved that movie, and the book was damn good. Baseball, magic, love... someone or other called this a male romance novel, and they&apos;re not far off, really. <br/><br/>Ray Kinsella is prompted by a Voice that comes from nowhere to build a baseball field in the middle of his farmland. Like most farmers, he&apos;s barely making it and can&apos;t really afford to lose the acreage. But he does it. <br/><br/>Strange and wonderful things happe</span>
  <span id="freeText17300561472869668514" style="display:none">I don't remember when I first read this. Probably shortly after Field of Dreams came out. I loved that movie, and the book was damn good. Baseball, magic, love... someone or other called this a male romance novel, and they're not far off, really. <br /><br />Ray Kinsella is prompted by a Voice that comes from nowhere to build a baseball field in the middle of his farmland. Like most farmers, he's barely making it and can't really afford to lose the acreage. But he does it. <br /><br />Strange and wonderful things happen, bringing magic to a small corner of Iowa. Ray connects with a legendary author and gets some surprises about his own family. It's a great story that, if it doesn't touch you at all, I truly feel sorry for you.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17300561472869668514" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
